The paper deals with low-density parity-check (LDPC) codes, which are commonly studied in the information theory (cs.IT) and coding theory (cs.FE) communities. The paper also proposes an efficient search algorithm, which involves graph theory and hierarchy, making it relevant to the sub-categories of cs.DS and cs.SI. Finally, the paper discusses the stopping distance of LDPC codes, which is a measure of their error-correcting capability, and this topic falls under the sub-category of cs.NI.
